The R programming language is our language of choice for data analysis. Not only is it open-source and freely-available, but it is capable of generating publication-quality images and has a large user-base amongst the scientific community. It also promotes the practice of \textbf{Reproducible Research}.
However, it comes with a steep learning-curve especially for those without prior exposure to command-line tools. Although it requires an investment of time, it is ultimately rewarding and a valuable skill to acquire. We are taking the following steps to help with the transition from GraphPad Prism.\vspace{1cm}

\begin{itemize}
\item{Promote availability of R classes at The Department of Genetics}
\item{Provide extra material to support the course in Genetics}
\item{Bespoke training on R graphics with online materials}
\item{Worked-examples of how to conduct typical GraphPad Prism analyses in R}
\item{Support forum for C.I. staff - {\color{crukpink}\textbf{\large{\tt http://bioinf-qa001/}}}}
\end{itemize}

